*Please note this opportunity is based in Canberra only, however we encourage applicants from any location to apply if they are willing to relocate to Canberra. Relocation support is available. 

Work for a department which connects and enriches every Australian community,
underpins our economy and society, and shapes the future of Australia's
infrastructure, transport, regional development, communications and creative
industries.  
  
If you're a motivated university graduate seeking an exciting and rewarding
start to your career, with the opportunity to improve the lives and
opportunities of Australians, we want to hear from you!  
  
As part of the graduate program you'll complete 3 challenging and diverse work
rotations across our high-profile and diverse portfolios, gain a Graduate
Certificate in either Public Admistration or in Policy and Data from the
University of Canberra, and progress from an APS 3 to APS 5 upon successful
completion of the program.  
  
For more information about the role and how to apply click the 'Apply' button.

